item.title: Dice Pencil Holder
item.creator: churuata
item.content:
Dice Pencil Holder - Description A German friend asked me to make a 3d model in the form of a dice. This is because his last name is "Würfel" which means "dice" in German. Because we are inclined to make functional models, that dice must fulfill a function. That's how our first pencil holder design came to light, the Dice Pencil Holder. A simple design of a dice but functional. The Dice Pencil Holder have 2 versions, a 8cm height version and a 10cm height version. In addition, a no-support version is available too.
These no-support version just add a 0.2mm top bridge in each hole. The support is quite easy to remove. In conclusion, these model is really easy to print, despite of the upper holes, with this little trick. Here you can find another Free Downloadable Pencil Holder. Which you can also download. We wish you a Happy printing!
This model is also available in parametric format. This means that the model can be modified according to your specific needs. You just need to have the Openscad program installed, which is Free Software, and change certain values in the "measurements_inc.scad" file. These files are only availables for our monthly supporters from www.buymeacoffee.com

53 connectors for any possibility of assembly.
Hinges.

Wall Supports.
45º Connectors.
And much more! Discover all the possibilities yourself.
STL Files Names Meanings:
L=Left
R=Right
45=45º
90=90º
W=Wall
F=Foot
T=Top
B=Bottom
MD=Middle
These combinations between these abbreviations. So, feel free to ask. In conclusion, with these kit you can have much fun a weekend, or even two. So, make it cool! Here you can find a 14mm version to download! We wish you a Happy printing!

item.content:

Because we are inclined to make functional models, that dice must fulfill a function. That's how our first pencil holder design came to light, the Dice Pencil Holder. A simple design of a dice but functional. The Dice Pencil Holder have 2 versions, a 8cm height version and a 10cm height version. In addition, a no-support version is available too.
These no-support version just add a 0.2mm top bridge in each hole. The support is quite easy to remove. In conclusion, these model is really easy to print, despite of the upper holes, with this little trick. Here you can find another Free Downloadable Pencil Holder. Which you can also download. Even protect your machine from dust let you invest your precious time in other things but cleaning.
So, now we can print this effective Openbuilds Lead CNC Simple Wheels Dust Cover for the upper wheels or for upper and under wheels. However, we recommend only for the upper wheels.
